7496	\begin{lemma}
7497	[The degree-\(p\) {\v C}ech backbone is the coproduct of intersection opens]
7498	  \label{lem:cech_backbone_left_sigma}
7499	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.cechBackbone_left_sigma}
7500	  \uses{def:cover_cech_nerve, def:cech_free_presheaf_complex}
7501	  Let \(\mathcal{U} : X = \bigcup_{i \in I} U_i\) be an open cover with cover arrow
7502	  \(q : \coprod_{i \in I} U_i \to X\), and let \(Y_p\) denote the degree-\(p\) object of the
7503	  {\v C}ech nerve \(\operatorname{coverCechNerveOver}\mathcal{U}\) of
7504	  Definition~\ref{def:cover_cech_nerve} --- the \((p+1)\)-fold fibre power of \(q\) over
7505	  \(X\). Then \(Y_p\) is canonically the coproduct
7506	  \[
7507	    Y_p \;\cong\; \coprod_{\sigma : \mathrm{Fin}(p+1) \to I} U_\sigma,
7508	    \qquad
7509	    U_\sigma \;=\; \operatorname{coverInterOpen}\mathcal{U}\,\sigma \;=\;
7510	      \bigcap_{k} U_{\sigma(k)},
7511	  \]
7512	  indexed by the multi-indices \(\sigma\), and the structure map \(q_p : Y_p \to X\) is
7513	  \(\operatorname{Sigma.desc}(\sigma \mapsto j_\sigma)\), where
7514	  \(j_\sigma : U_\sigma \hookrightarrow X\) is the open immersion of the intersection open
7515	  \(U_\sigma\) of Definition~\ref{def:cech_free_presheaf_complex}. In words: the fibre power
7516	  of the open immersions \(U_i \hookrightarrow X\) is the intersection open, and the disjoint
7517	  union over \(\sigma\) assembles the {\v C}ech backbone.
7518	\end{lemma}
7519	\begin{proof}
7520	  \uses{def:cover_cech_nerve, def:cech_free_presheaf_complex}
7521	  The coproduct \(\coprod_i U_i\) has, in degree \(p\), the \((p+1)\)-fold fibre power over
7522	  \(X\); fibre products distribute over coproducts, so \(\bigl(\coprod_i U_i\bigr)^{\times_X
7523	  (p+1)} \cong \coprod_{\sigma : \mathrm{Fin}(p+1) \to I} U_{\sigma(0)} \times_X \cdots
7524	  \times_X U_{\sigma(p)}\). Each factor \(U_{\sigma(k)} \hookrightarrow X\) is an open
7525	  immersion, and the fibre product of open immersions over \(X\) is the intersection of
7526	  their images, so \(U_{\sigma(0)} \times_X \cdots \times_X U_{\sigma(p)} \cong \bigcap_k
7527	  U_{\sigma(k)} = U_\sigma\). Under this identification the structure map of the
7528	  \(\sigma\)-component is the open immersion \(j_\sigma\), and the universal map out of the
7529	  coproduct is \(\operatorname{Sigma.desc}(\sigma \mapsto j_\sigma)\).
7530	\end{proof}
