7644	\begin{lemma}
7645	[The evaluated augmented {\v C}ech complex is the concrete section {\v C}ech complex]
7646	  \label{lem:cechSection_complex_iso}
7647	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.cechSection_complex_iso}
7648	  \uses{lem:pushPull_eval_prod_iso, lem:section_cech_objd_apply,
7649	    lem:section_cech_product_equiv, def:cech_augmented_complex}
7650	  Fix an open \(V \subseteq X\). The augmented {\v C}ech complex of
7651	  Definition~\ref{def:cech_augmented_complex} evaluated at \(V\) (through
7652	  \(\operatorname{toPresheaf}\)) --- call it \(D^\bullet\), the cochain complex of abelian
7653	  groups with \(D^p = \Gamma(V, \operatorname{pushPullObj}\mathcal{F}\,Y_p)\) --- is
7654	  isomorphic, as a cochain complex, to the concrete section {\v C}ech complex \(D'^\bullet\)
7655	  over the family \(\bigl(\operatorname{coverInterOpen}\mathcal{U}\,\cdot \cap V\bigr)\): the
7656	  complex with \(D'^p = \prod_\sigma \Gamma(U_\sigma \cap V, \mathcal{F})\) and the
7657	  alternating coface restriction differential. The isomorphism is the degreewise map of
7658	  Lemma~\ref{lem:pushPull_eval_prod_iso}, and it intertwines the two differentials.
7659	\end{lemma}
7660	\begin{proof}
7661	  \uses{lem:pushPull_eval_prod_iso, lem:section_cech_objd_apply,
7662	    lem:section_cech_product_equiv}
7663	  In each degree \(p\) the object isomorphism \(D^p \cong D'^p\) is
7664	  Lemma~\ref{lem:pushPull_eval_prod_iso}. It remains to check the degreewise isomorphisms
7665	  commute with the differentials. The differential of \(D'^\bullet\) is, read through the
7666	  product equivalence \(\operatorname{sectionCechProductEquiv}\)
7667	  (Lemma~\ref{lem:section_cech_product_equiv}), the alternating sum of presheaf face
7668	  restrictions \(\sum_i (-1)^i\, \operatorname{sectionCechFaceRestr}(\sigma, i)\) computed in
7669	  Lemma~\ref{lem:section_cech_objd_apply}. The differential of \(D^\bullet\) is the
7670	  evaluation at \(V\) of the {\v C}ech-nerve coface maps, assembled from the same push--pull
7671	  restriction comparisons; under the degreewise identification each coface of \(D^\bullet\)
7672	  becomes the corresponding face restriction of \(D'^\bullet\), so the alternating sums
7673	  agree. Reusing the alternating-sum bookkeeping of Lemma~\ref{lem:section_cech_objd_apply}
7674	  --- rather than rebuilding it --- matches the differentials and yields the isomorphism of
7675	  complexes.
7676	\end{proof}
