7794	\begin{lemma}
7795	[Cohomology sheaf is the sheafification of the objectwise homology]
7796	  \label{lem:cohomology_sheaf_is_sheafify_homology}
7797	  \lean{PresheafOfModules.homologyIsoSheafify,
7798	    PresheafOfModules.counitComplexIso,
7799	    PresheafOfModules.sheafificationAdditive,
7800	    CategoryTheory.Functor.mapHomologyIso'}
7801	  % NOTE: project-built generalization. Stacks Tag~01XJ
7802	  % (\texttt{lemma-describe-higher-direct-images}) establishes the consequence
7803	  % $R^if_*\mathcal{F} \cong \text{sheafification of }(V \mapsto H^i(f^{-1}(V),\mathcal{F}))$
7804	  % but does not state sheafification commuting with the homology of an arbitrary
7805	  % cochain complex as a standalone lemma. No verbatim Stacks source quote for this block.
7806	  Let \(K\) be a cochain complex of presheaves of modules over a site admitting
7807	  sheafification. For every index \(i\) there is a natural
7808	  isomorphism between the \(i\)-th homology of the sheafified complex and the
7809	  sheafification of the \(i\)-th objectwise (presheaf-level) homology of \(K\),
7810	  \[
7811	    H^i\bigl(\operatorname{sheafify}(K)\bigr)
7812	      \;\cong\;
7813	    \operatorname{sheafify}\bigl(H^i(K)\bigr).
7814	  \]
7815	  Equivalently, sheafification commutes with the formation of homology. This is the
7816	  reusable engine underlying the presheaf description of the higher direct images
